    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2920.0,
      "end_time": 5460.0,
      "text": "Why are auroras formed?"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 7940.0,
      "end_time": 11020.0,
      "text": "Maybe because the earth forgets to switch off the lights."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 11140.0,
      "end_time": 12080.0,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 12140.0,
      "end_time": 13200.0,
      "text": "Let me explain."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 15180.0,
      "end_time": 17260.0,
      "text": "Our sun is a giant burning star."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 17540.0,
      "end_time": 19900.0,
      "text": "It expels tons of solar wind into space."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 20340.0,
      "end_time": 23680.0,
      "text": "Solar wind consists of super hot charged particles which are fatal."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 24400.0,
      "end_time": 27900.0,
      "text": "So, should we use a big umbrella to protect\nourselves from these particles?"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 28940.0,
      "end_time": 29700.0,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 30620.0,
      "end_time": 33800.0,
      "text": "The earth's magnetic field acts like a shield and protects us."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 34120.0,
      "end_time": 38280.0,
      "text": "Its field lines appear to emerge from the south pole and merge into the north pole."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 38760.0,
      "end_time": 43380.0,
      "text": "Now, when the charged particles hit our magnetic field, most of them get deflected."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 43980.0,
      "end_time": 50320.0,
      "text": "However, some of them flow along the earth's magnetic field lines to the poles and reach our upper atmosphere."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 50920.0,
      "end_time": 53900.0,
      "text": "Here, these particles collide with oxygen\nand nitrogen."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 54320.0,
      "end_time": 59060.0,
      "text": "This causes them to give off various colors of light which are called auroras."
    }
  ]
